node.text:
If you miss my weekly vlogs, this week’s podcast episode is for you! 🎙️

In case you didn’t know, @theletteredclassroom and I have a podcast together called Teaching to the TOP where we share all things time management, organization, and productivity for teachers! 😍

Last week I recorded a “week in the life” podcast episode where I check in each day and share all about my intentions for the day, what I actually got done, and more! It’s basically like a weekly vlog but in audio form 😂

You can check it out using the link in my profile or by searching “Teaching to the TOP” wherever you listen to your favorite podcasts! 🎧

node.text:
Pantry: organized ✅

For the past 7 years, we have had a pantry the size of a shoe box (slight exaggeration but also fully accurate 😂). The pantry in our new hours is MASSIVE so I gave myself full permission to create our dream pantry 😍

After multiple trips to @thecontainerstore, countless @thehomeedit bins purchased, and approximately 152 rearrangements, our pantry is exactly what I have always dreamed of! 🖤🎉

I created a full video documenting the process and it’s live on my channel for you to watch! 🎥

You can check it out using the link in my profile or the link below:
bit.ly/teachervlog290

node.text:
SWIPE TO SEE THE BEFORE ➡️😳

First of all, prepare yourself for an influx of house posts because being a first time homeowner is a new, exciting season in our lives and I’m embracing every second of it. No apologies 💁🏻‍♀️

Second, I love a good before and after 😍 When we moved in, we became obsessed with our kitchen. It’s double the size of our old kitchen and gets tons of natural light! 💡

Neither @mrpocketfulofprimary or myself have ever been overly handy. I mean, we can hardcore put together a piece of IKEA furniture but beyond that we are out of our element 😂

We knew we wanted to make some changes in our kitchen to make it fit our style so YouTube tutorials became our best friend 😂🎥

Over the past 2 weeks, we’ve learned how to wire lights, install hardware, and paint tile floors. Honestly, I’m super proud of us.

We did this! It isn’t perfect but it was done by us and I love that 🖤

Details:
Floor paint: @rustoleum Floor Coating Kit
Lights: @amazon
Hardware: @amazon
Table, chairs, & rug: @wayfair

node.text:
Are you team solid color bins 🎨 or clear bins 🤍?!

I feel like this question is extremely divisive! 😬

Want to know a secret? I’m both 😂 I’m team solid color bins for organizing items that are on display in my classroom (to add some color and make my room brighter) but team clear bins for organizing items in my cabinets (so I can easily see what’s inside).

I’m also both when it comes to my house! I’m team solid color bins for items that are stored in my garage (because I want to hide the mess… real talk) but team clear bins for items in my pantry/closets (so again, I can easily see what’s inside).

Which one are you (and bonus points for explaining why)?!

* Both sets of bins pictured are from @lakeshorelearning 😍🎉 *

node.text:
BEFORE 👉🏼 AFTER

So many memories have been made in this classroom 🖤 It is officially time to close the door on this current adventure while simultaneously saying hello to new opportunities and experiences.

I am beyond grateful to my students, their families, and my coworkers for helping me grow into the teacher I am today. I am leaving my school as a better teacher than when I walked into it and I am forever thankful for that 🙌🏼

Here’s to staying connected with the relationships I formed because once my student, always my student. It’s not goodbye… it’s only see you later 🖤

node.text:
My coworkers kick AXE! 🪓😂

Cheesy puns aside, my coworkers truly are the best and I have been so lucky to work with them over the past several years! 🖤 

Shoutout to @laurwhite19 for organizing this surprise! 🎉 Even with the stress of the end of the year, changing grades, and moving classrooms, you took the time to put this together and made me feel so special. Best team teacher award!🥇

In case you were looking for the perfect way to end the school year, it’s definitely axe throwing! 😂 Best stress reliever EVER!
